======================================================================
PART 9: THE COMPLETE NUMBER MAP
    1, 2, 3, 7, 8, 10, 11 — positions in the universe
======================================================================

THE MAP:

  NUMBER  BINARY  ROLE IN TOURNAMENT THEORY
  ------  ------  -------------------------
    1      1      Identity / empty sum / weight of ∅
    2      10     OCF evaluation point (x=2), k-nacci limit
    3      11     Secondary root, 3-cycle length, w-k-nacci limit
    7      111    Jacobsthal-Lucas j(3), last 'pure' n
    8      1000   2³, first cross-level n, Q divisor
    10     1010   Base of our numeral system, I(CG,10) interpolates
    11     1011   First prime after 8, first perfect α₃ packing

BINARY STRUCTURE:
  1    = 1
  2    = 10     (1 shifted)
  3    = 11     (1 shifted + 1)
  7    = 111    (three 1s = 2³-1)
  8    = 1000   (1 shifted 3 positions)
  10   = 1010   (2 interleaved with itself: 1_1_ = 10·10)
  11   = 1011   (2 interleaved with 3: 10·11)

THE RECURRENCE VIEW:
  Each number defines a recurrence level:

  n | recurrence                    | dominant root | meaning
  --+-------------------------------+---------------+---------
  1 | f(n)=f(n-1)                   | 1             | constant
  2 | f(n)=f(n-1)+f(n-2)            | φ≈1.618       | Fibonacci
  3 | f(n)=f(n-1)+f(n-2)+f(n-3)     | 1.839...      | tribonacci
  7 | 7-nacci                       | 1.992...      | almost 2
  8 | 8-nacci                       | 1.996...      | very close to 2
  10| 10-nacci                      | 1.999...      | essentially 2
  11| 11-nacci                      | 1.9995...     | essentially 2

  And the WEIGHTED versions:
  n | weighted n-nacci root | gap to 3
  --+-----------------------+---------
   1| 1.000                 | 2.000
   2| 2.0000000000        | 1.00e+00
   3| 2.4675038571        | 5.32e-01
   7| 2.9311424638        | 6.89e-02
   8| 2.9560974219        | 4.39e-02
  10| 2.9815553148        | 1.84e-02
  11| 2.9879140484        | 1.21e-02

THE GRAND SYNTHESIS:

  'If one understands 2 and 3, one has the keys to the universe.'

  This is because:
  • 2 and 3 are the limits of ALL k-nacci recurrences
  • Every tournament invariant decomposes into 2-adic and 3-adic parts
  • H = I(CG, 2) = 1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂ + ...  (powers of 2)
  • H = b₀ + 3b₁ + 9b₂ + ...              (powers of 3, beta basis)
  • The 2-adic tower: H mod 2, mod 4, mod 8, ...  (Rédei, cycle parity, ...)
  • The 3-adic tower: H mod 3, mod 9, mod 27, ... (topology, derivative, ...)
  • Q = (H² - Pf²)/8: divisor 8 = 2³
  • Jacobsthal denominators: 3, 5, 7, ... = odd cycle lengths
  • Gap convergence rates: 1/2 and 2/3

  (7, 8) = (2³-1, 2³) is where CROSS-LEVEL coupling begins,
  making the two Jacobsthal levels interact for the first time.

  (10, 11) in base 2 is (1010, 1011) = the INTERLEAVING of (2,3).
  In recurrence space, they sit between Jacobsthal levels k=3 and k=4,
  exactly where the 5-cycle structure meets the 7-cycle structure.
  In tournament space, n=11 is the first perfect 3-part packing (3+3+5=11).

